text.tspan: Who Americans spend their time with, by age, United States, 15 to 80
Average time spent with others is measured in minutes per day, and shown by the age of the respondent. This is
based on averages from surveys between 2009 and 2019.
Source: American Time Use Survey (2009-2019) and Lindberg (2017)
Note: Relationships used to categorize people are not exhaustive. Additionally, time spent with multiple people can be counted more than once
(e.g. attending a party with friends and partner counts for both friends and partner).
